				<name type="primary" sortindex="5" value="The Big Job" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>I&amp;rsquo;ve got a new job for you and your crew. There&amp;rsquo;s this new bank called the Mega Bank. The bank itself consists of 4 giant vaults. There must be millions stored in each. Your job is to find those vaults, stuff as much money down your pockets, and get out before you get busted. The police are stationed all around the bank. So you have to be careful. For the entire year, we can make this bank our primary target. So what do you say, are you in?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Welcome to The Big Job. The card game that tests your luck and greed to become rich. Are you lucky enough to hit the jackpot and avoid detection? Drawing the million dollar card and leaving with what you've got sounds like a lucky way to get rich. Or do you hunger the greed and adrenaline rush of taking hostages and pulling off some big time cash while dodging the police? Clearing out all the vaults and ransoming up a hostage for millions of dollars sounds right up your alley. Just try not to get busted in the process. It's going to cost ya! Grab your crew and lets head out for the big job!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you're looking for a snatch and grab game to play with family and friends that requires no strategy, just sheer luck and greed, The Big Job is the perfect game for you. The Big Job is very easy to learn and play with others. Setup 4 decks and then just take turns pulling cards. Sounds very simple right? If only pulling money from a deck of cards was real. While the chances of getting caught are slim your greed will be your demise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As The Big Job may seem like a very simple game with no strategy what so ever, it will keep you immersed with greed and other players&amp;rsquo; demises. Trust us the only player that can hurt you is you. So make sure you choose wisely, whether it&amp;rsquo;s to keep drawing money or to just call it quits.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
